<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Chile, Brazil in America Cup Semis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CIUDAD DEL ESTE, Paraguay, (AP) -- Ronaldo and Rivaldo scored,  
and Dida saved a penalty kick for the second time in the tournament 
as Brazil beat Argentina 2-1 Sunday and advanced to the semifinals 
of the America Cup, South America's soccer championship. 
</P>
<P>
	Argentina went ahead in the 10th minute when a long shot by Juan  
Pablo Sorin bounced off the knee of defender Joao Carlos and into 
the net. 
</P>
<P>
	Rivaldo tied it with a free kick in the 32nd minute after Cafu  
was tripped at the top of the penalty area. Ronaldo then scored the 
go-ahead goal three minutes into the second half after Emerson 
streaked up the middle and passed to Ze Roberto, who left the ball 
for the oncoming forward. 
</P>
<P>
	Dido saved the penalty kick by Roberto Ayala with 13 minutes  
remaining. He also stopped a penalty kick during a 1-0 win over 
Chile in the first round. 
</P>
<P>
	Brazil plays Mexico in the semifinals on Wednesday. A day  
earlier, Chile plays Paraguay in the first semifinal. 
</P>
<P>
	In Sunday's other game, Pedro Reyes scored twice and Ivan  
Zamorano got the go-ahead goal as Chile upset Columbia 3-2 at 
Luque. 
</P>
<P>
	As Marcelo Salas sat out the second game of a two-game  
suspension, Chile twice came from behind. 
</P>
<P>
	After Jorge Bolano's goal put Columbia ahead in the seventh  
minute, Reyes tied it in the 25th with a header off Jose Luis 
Sierra's corner kick. 
</P>
<P>
	Victor Bonilla put Colombia back ahead 10 minutes later, tapping  
the ball past goalkeeper Marcelo Ramirez. 
</P>
<P>
	Reyes tied it again four minutes into the second half when he  
headed in a perfect cross from Sierra. Zamorano put Chile ahead in 
the 64th, slipping through the defense and eluding goalkeeper 
Miguel Calero with a subtle feint. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
