<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-11 17:00:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Ascot Yael Wins Dance Smartly Stakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- Drawing away in the late stretch, Ascot Yael won  
the $110,800 Dance Smartly Stakes by three-quarters of a length 
over Skytrial on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Ascot Yael, the 5-year-old daughter of Ascot Knight, ran the  
1 1/8-mile race at Woodbine in 1:47.25 over a turf course rated firm. 
</P>
<P>
	Ascot Yael returned $20.30, $7.90, $4.90. Skytrial paid $3.10,  
$2.30, and No Foul Play paid $4.40 for finishing third. 
</P>
<P>
	Owned by Syd Cooper's R.M.C Stable, Ascot Yael raised her career  
earnings to $289,069. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
