<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Schumacher Breaks Leg at British GP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SILVERSTONE, England (AP) -- Michael Schumacher lasted just 30  
seconds at the British Grand Prix on Sunday, breaking his leg in a 
crash that could possibly sideline him for the season. 
</P>
<P>
	The two-time world champion had surgery on his right leg, which  
was broken in two places. There were no head or spinal injuries. 
</P>
<P>
	Doctors at Northampton Hosptial said there were no complications  
and the 30-year-old driver is expected to be released Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	The accident happened after Schumacher came out of a turn and  
his brakes seemed to lock. He barreled across the track into a wall 
at about 130 mph but was able to climb out of his crumpled Ferrari 
and wave to a few fans. 
</P>
<P>
	His team said a failed power steering unit probably caused the  
crash. 
</P>
<P>
	Schumacher was placed on a stretcher and carried to an  
ambulance. He reportedly called his wife to reassure her. 
</P>
<P>
	The restart of the race, won eventually by McLaren's David  
Coulthard, was delayed 40 minutes as Schumacher's car was taken 
from track. 
</P>
<P>
	The injury is sure to keep Schumacher out of several races and  
hinder the German's chances of winning this year's series title. 
</P>
<P>
	The front end of his red Ferrari folded like an accordion. The  
car hit a three-layer deep tire barrier after Schumacher had been 
slowed going through a gravel shoulder. 
</P>
<P>
	Schumacher's crash came as the red flag went up. The start of  
the race had to be abandoned and restarted as two cars stalled on 
the starting line. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
