<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Pyewacket Finishes Transpac Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HONOLULU (AP) -- Roy Disney's Pyewacket had a record crossing in  
the 40th Transpacific Yacht Race, but Grand Illusion apparently had 
the fastest overall corrected handicap time. 
</P>
<P>
	The 72-foot Pyewacket out of the Los Angeles Yacht Club sailed  
past the Diamond Head finish line at 9:41 p.m. Saturday to win 
first-to-finish honors in the voyage from Los Angeles to Honolulu. 
</P>
<P>
	The maxi sled finished the 2,225-mile race in 7 days, 11 hours,  
41 minutes, 27 seconds, taking 3 hours, 43 minutes, 5 seconds off 
the record set by Disney's smaller Pyewacket in the 1997 race. 
</P>
<P>
	Disney said it became clear halfway through the race that his  
boat was on a record pace. 
</P>
<P>
	Doug Baker's 68-foot turbo sled Magnitude from the Long Beach  
Yacht Club of California also broke the 1997 record, finishing 1 
hour, 5 minutes, 40 seconds behind Pyewacket. 
</P>
<P>
	Grand Illusion, representing the Lahaina Yacht Club of Hawaii,  
finished at 12:52 p.m. Sunday, beating Pyewacket by almost three 
hours on corrected time. 
</P>
<P>
	Only two other boats in the race, Gone With the Wind from San  
Francisco and Stealth Chicken from Long Beach, had an outside 
chance of besting Grand Illusion, race officials said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
