<HEADLINE> 7 Ejected in Mariners-Dodgers Brawl </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- A brushback pitch by Seattle's Frankie  
Rodriguez triggered a bench-clearing brawl Sunday that led to seven 
ejections in the Mariners' game against the Los Angeles Dodgers. 
</P>
<P>
	Mariners relievers Damaso Marte, Jose Mesa and Jose Paniagua  
were ejected along with outfielder Jay Buhner, who is on the 
disabled list. Dodgers catcher Todd Hundley was ejected along with 
teammate Pedro Borbon and bullpen coach Rick Dempsey. 
</P>
<P>
	The brawl, which interrupted the game for 15 minutes, began  
after Trenidad Hubbard hit a three-run double in the sixth inning 
and Rodriguez's next pitch went at Mark Grudzielanek's head. 
</P>
<P>
	Words were exchanged and the reliever made a motion at  
Grudzielanek, as though he was inviting him to charge the mound. 
The dugouts and bullpens emptied, and fights broke out as the brawl 
spilled over toward the warning track in front of the Mariners' 
dugout. 
</P>
<P>
	Fans littered the outfield with debris. Order was restored but  
benches emptied again when Hundley shouted toward the mound and 
made a gesture before Rodriguez started his warmup throws. 
</P>
<P>
	No punches were thrown in the second incident. Dodgers catcher  
Angel Pena injured his left arm in the fighting and was replaced by 
Hubbard, who had been in left field. It was Hubbard's major league 
debut behind the plate. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
