<HEADLINE> Joel, Brinkley in No-Nukes Protest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WATERFORD, Conn. (AP) -- Billy Joel and Christie Brinkley were  
back together again over the weekend, not as husband and wife, but 
for an anti-nuclear protest carrying warnings about radiation from 
the deck of boat. 
</P>
<P>
	The divorced singer and supermodel reunited Saturday for a  
protest cruise on Long Island Sound against against the Millstone 
nuclear power plants. At the same time, anti-nuclear advocates 
stood on shore calling for a shutdown of the reactors. 
</P>
<P>
	Both celebrities are members of STAR -- Standing for Truth About  
Radiation. 
</P>
<P>
	The protesters want the Millstone plants shut down permanently.  
Earlier this year, two of the reactors were allowed back into 
operation after three years of safety concerns. 
  	   	
</P>
