	'American Pie' Tops Box Office  
</P>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- ``American Pie'' brought in $18.1 million in  
ticket sales over the weekend for the number one spot in the box 
office. The raunchy teen comedy pushed Will Smith's critically 
savaged ``Wild Wild West'' into second place. ``Arlington Road,'' 
the only other movie opening in wide release, debuted with a 
disappointing $7.4 million, industry estimates showed today. The 
loose remake of the old ``Wild Wild West'' TV show lost a 
devastating 40 percent of its audience after two weeks. 

</P>
