<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Rapper DMX Arrested in Trinidad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PORT-OF-SPAIN, Trinidad (AP) -- American rapper DMX was arrested  
on obscenity charges during a concert in Trinidad, prompting a 
bottle-throwing protest by his fans in the audience, authorities 
said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Police who led DMX from the stage Saturday night fired their  
guns into the air to control the angry crowd. 
</P>
<P>
	DMX, whose real name is Earl Simmons, was being held in jail  
Sunday pending a court appearance Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Using obscene language in public is illegal in this conservative  
Caribbean country. Police stopped a concert by hip-hop singer Foxy 
Brown on July 3 over similar allegations, but no charges were 
filed. 
</P>
<P>
	It was unclear Sunday what words Simmons was charged with using.  
</P>
<P>
	Cigarette company Craven A, a sponsor of the concert at the  
Queen's Park Oval cricket ground in Port-of-Spain, said the rapper 
was warned that profanity could lead to his ``arrest and removal.'' 
</P>
<P>
	It is the latest in a series of recent brushes with the law for  
the 28-year-old rapper. Last month, he was charged in New Jersey 
with possession of illegal firearms and ammunition. He is also free 
on bail in connection with an assault charge in Yonkers, New York. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
