<HEADLINE> Galaxy 5, Revolution 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FOXBORO, Mass. (AP) -- Roy Myers scored the go-ahead goal in the  
72nd minute, and the Los Angeles Galaxy went on to beat the New 
England Revolution 5-2 Sunday in Major League Soccer. 
</P>
<P>
	Myers' goal gave Los Angeles a 3-2 lead. Cobi Jones scored in  
the 85th minute and Carlos Hermosillo added a goal off a Jones pass 
in the final minute for Los Angeles (10-7). 
</P>
<P>
	Ezra Hendrickson and Clint Mathis also scored for the Galaxy.  
Joe-Max Moore scored twice for New England (8-9), giving him six 
goals in his last four games and a team-high 10. 
</P>
<P>
	Moore's diving header of Ted Chronopolos' indirect kick put New  
England ahead in the 39th minute, but Mathis beat Walter Zenga to 
tie it a minute later. 
</P>
<P>
	An unmarked Hendrickson gave Los Angeles a 2-1 lead in the 63rd  
minute off a cross from Mauricio Cienfuegos. Moore converted a 
penalty kick three minutes later after Greg Vanney was called for a 
hard tackle on Johnny Torres in the penalty area. 
  	   	
</P>
