<HEADLINE> Woodbridge Pulls Out of Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SYDNEY, Australia (AP) -- Doubles specialist Todd Woodbridge  
broke up the Woodies for this week's Davis Cup quarterfinal against 
the United States when he withdrew from the team. 
</P>
<P>
	Captain John Newcombe said Woodbridge, who forms one of the  
world's top doubles units with Mark Woodforde, decided to withdraw 
Monday because of a minor arm injury and a loss of form. 
</P>
<P>
	Newcombe said he would have preferred Woodbridge stayed in the  
team but said the player felt he would let his teammates down in 
the tie at Longwood Cricket Club in Brookline, Mass. 
</P>
<P>
	Woodbridge was replaced by Sandon Stolle, who is ranked No. 3 in  
the world in doubles, but Patrick Rafter might be called in to 
partner Woodforde or Stolle. 
</P>
<P>
	The Australian team is already missing U.S. Open finalist Mark  
Philippoussis, who withdrew from his Wimbledon quarterfinal against 
Pete Sampras with a knee injury. The tie starts Friday with 
Australia facing a strong American team of Todd Martin, Jim 
Courier, Pete Sampras and Alex O'Brien. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
