<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Forestry Wins Dwyer Stakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Jerry Bailey rode the winner of Belmont Park's  
$150,000 Dwyer stakes for the third time in its last four runnings 
when he guided favored Forestry to a 2 1/4 length victory in Sunday's 
82nd renewal of the event. 
</P>
<P>
	Doneraile Court finished second of six another one-half length  
before Successful Appeal. 
</P>
<P>
	Bailey's other Dwyer winners were Victory Speech in 1996 and  
Behrens the following year. 
</P>
<P>
	Doneraile Court went the first half-mile in 44:4 and  
three-quarters in 1:08:2 with Forestry shadowing him. Once into the 
stretch, Forestry took over and held on the rest of the way. 
</P>
<P>
	Forestry finished the 1 1/16 miles in 1:41 on the fast track to  
earn $90,000 for Aaron U. and Marie D. Jones. It was the sixth win 
in eight starts this year for the colt by Storm Cat from the 
Pleasant Colony mare, Shared Interest. 
</P>
<P>
	The winner returned $4.00,$2.30 and $2.10. Doneraile Court paid  
$2.60 and $2.10 and Successful Appeal was $2.10 to show. 
</P>
